209
00:12:01,517 --> 00:12:03,817
Four henchmen?

210
00:12:03,817 --> 00:12:05,317
Don't tell me...

211
00:12:05,317 --> 00:12:08,717
Hurry and open that door up

212
00:12:08,717 --> 00:12:10,917
so that the officers can pursue Kid!

213
00:12:10,917 --> 00:12:14,017
No, I can't open the door.

214
00:12:14,017 --> 00:12:15,217
Why not?

215
00:12:15,217 --> 00:12:21,417
I can't help feeling that he's still here in the room somewhere.

216
00:12:21,417 --> 00:12:22,617
I can't shake the feeling

217
00:12:22,617 --> 00:12:26,817
that he's waiting for the door to open any minute.

218
00:12:26,817 --> 00:12:30,817
Exactly. Don't open the door.

219
00:12:32,217 --> 00:12:36,817
Because he's probably surprised at what a tough time

220
00:12:36,817 --> 00:12:39,717
