240
00:13:29,617 --> 00:13:31,717
That's true.

241
00:13:31,717 --> 00:13:35,417
But can the giraffe statue be taken out without using the key?

242
00:13:35,417 --> 00:13:38,417
It's written at the foot of the pillar, see?

243
00:13:38,417 --> 00:13:40,417
"One who desires to acquire the giraffe

244
00:13:40,417 --> 00:13:42,817
without using the correct method,

245
00:13:42,817 --> 00:13:45,717
must move with the flow."

246
00:13:45,717 --> 00:13:48,817
This is the after care that Kichiemon Samizu

247
00:13:48,817 --> 00:13:52,317
left behind in case the keys are lost.

248
00:13:52,317 --> 00:13:56,317
It means anyone who wants to get a hold of the giraffe horns

249
00:13:56,417 --> 00:13:59,217
without relying on the keys, should go with the flow.

250
00:13:59,217 --> 00:14:01,117
What flow?

251
00:14:01,117 --> 00:14:02,417
The four gods...

252
00:14:02,417 --> 00:14:03,917
The pedestals in the four corners,

253
00:14:03,917 --> 00:14:07,017
each represent the legendary deities belonging to the pedestals.

254
00:14:08,717 --> 00:14:12,917
This green pedestal represents the Blue Dragon.

255
00:14:12,917 --> 00:14:15,017
The white pedestal, the White Tiger!

256
00:14:15,017 --> 00:14:17,017
The black one is the Black Tortoise!

257
00:14:17,017 --> 00:14:20,817
And this red pedestal represents the Vermilion Bird!

258
00:14:20,817 --> 00:14:25,917
But I wonder if there was a specific order to the four gods?

259
00:14:25,917 --> 00:14:28,317
-Seasons! -Seasons?

260
00:14:28,317 --> 00:14:30,317
The Blue Dragon is Spring.

261
00:14:30,317 --> 00:14:32,317
Vermilion Bird, Summer.

262
00:14:32,317 --> 00:14:34,217
The White Tiger, Autumn.

263
00:14:34,217 --> 00:14:36,517
