264
00:14:36,517 --> 00:14:39,917
If "must move with the flow", means...

265
00:14:39,917 --> 00:14:43,217
move along with the flow of the seasons.

266
00:14:43,217 --> 00:14:44,917
It means to move your body

267
00:14:44,917 --> 00:14:47,317
in order of Spring, Summer, Autumn and Winter!

268
00:14:47,317 --> 00:14:49,017
Move your body?

269
00:14:49,017 --> 00:14:52,217
In other words, bring your body close to the pedestal like this

270
00:14:52,217 --> 00:14:55,017
and tilt your body.

271
00:14:55,017 --> 00:14:57,017
Next, it's you, Ai!

272
00:14:57,017 --> 00:14:59,017
Yes.

273
00:14:59,017 --> 00:15:00,617
Okay, Ayumi.

274
00:15:00,617 --> 00:15:03,117
Yep.

275
00:15:03,117 --> 00:15:04,917
Lastly, it's you, Genta!

276
00:15:04,917 --> 00:15:06,417
Aye!

277
00:15:11,917 --> 00:15:13,317
The pillar...

278
00:15:13,317 --> 00:15:14,717
Is moving...

279
00:15:14,717 --> 00:15:16,617
And closing.

280
00:15:20,817 --> 00:15:23,517
It... It's closed!

281
00:15:23,517 --> 00:15:25,117
Now you know

282
00:15:25,117 --> 00:15:26,817
that you can make the pillar go up and down

283
00:15:26,817 --> 00:15:29,417
even without the keys.

284
00:15:29,417 --> 00:15:32,317
But it only blacked-out for a mere minute!

285
00:15:32,317 --> 00:15:35,517
Are you saying that Kid during this time

286
00:15:35,517 --> 00:15:37,217
ran around the room without any light,

287
00:15:37,217 --> 00:15:41,117
stuck cards to all the pedestals and tilted them?

288
00:15:41,117 --> 00:15:45,317
Kid didn't. We're the ones who tilted them.

289
00:15:45,317 --> 00:15:48,117
Because we were told to guard keyholes of

290
00:15:48,117 --> 00:15:51,717
the green, red, white and black pedestals.

291
00:15:51,717 --> 00:15:55,717
Isn't that right, Inspector Nakamori?

292
00:15:55,717 --> 00:15:59,717
Rather... Mr. Magician under the Moonlight?

293
00:16:01,017 --> 00:16:02,617
I see.

294
00:16:02,617 --> 00:16:04,717
In order to guard the keyhole,

295
00:16:04,717 --> 00:16:07,117
you'd have to bring your back close to the pedestal,

296
00:16:07,117 --> 00:16:10,717
and guard the surroundings.

297
00:16:10,717 --> 00:16:11,917
Hey, hey.

298
00:16:11,917 --> 00:16:14,217
Then just how in the world did I stick the cards on?

299
00:16:14,217 --> 00:16:17,017
He made us do that, too!

300
00:16:17,017 --> 00:16:18,517
By cracking the window,

301
00:16:18,517 --> 00:16:20,017
letting the rain and wind come in

302
00:16:20,017 --> 00:16:21,817
and making us wear our hoods.

303
00:16:21,817 --> 00:16:23,317
He made us stick the cards

304
00:16:23,317 --> 00:16:26,317
with a sticky seal on them that were hidden inside the hood

305
00:16:26,317 --> 00:16:29,317
and stuck to our backs when we leaned against the pedestals!

306
00:16:29,317 --> 00:16:32,517
As proof of that, the position the cards are pasted on,

307
00:16:32,517 --> 00:16:34,217
each correspond to the height of the one

308
00:16:34,217 --> 00:16:36,417
who was guarding the pedestal, right?

309
00:16:36,417 --> 00:16:39,317
Now that you mentioned it...

310
00:16:39,317 --> 00:16:42,117
Kid most probably called Advisor Suzuki

311
00:16:42,117 --> 00:16:44,817
using the voice of the reporter told him

312
00:16:44,817 --> 00:16:48,617
that he would introduce a company that sold the parkas,

313
00:16:48,617 --> 00:16:51,717
and planted tricks on them himself.

314
00:16:51,717 --> 00:16:54,017
But it's amazing how the cards were stuck

315
00:16:54,017 --> 00:16:56,017
onto the corresponding pedestals in the dark,

316
00:16:56,017 --> 00:16:58,217
without making a mistake.

317
00:16:58,217 --> 00:17:00,717
As far as what was seen on the VTR,

318
00:17:00,717 --> 00:17:03,717
there was nothing like a signal.

319
00:17:03,717 --> 00:17:04,917
Sound...

320
00:17:04,917 --> 00:17:06,917
He told us!

321
00:17:06,917 --> 00:17:12,717
To wait for the sound of the electricity flowing

322
00:17:12,717 --> 00:17:14,117
through the pedestals turn off,

323
00:17:14,117 --> 00:17:16,717
then, to guard the pedestals in that order!

324
00:17:16,717 --> 00:17:19,717
I didn't set up such a sound though.

325
00:17:19,717 --> 00:17:21,617
Of course there was!

326
00:17:21,617 --> 00:17:22,917
It beeped.

327
00:17:22,917 --> 00:17:24,717
An irritating sound.

328
00:17:24,717 --> 00:17:27,317
-Did you hear such a sound? -No.

329
00:17:27,317 --> 00:17:28,817
Not at all.

330
00:17:28,817 --> 00:17:30,517
What?

331
00:17:32,117 --> 00:17:34,317
Mosquito sound.

332
00:17:35,617 --> 00:17:37,217
A high frequency sound

333
00:17:37,217 --> 00:17:40,717
that gradually becomes inaudible to people over the age of 20

334
00:17:40,717 --> 00:17:42,817
because the ears start to age.

335
00:17:42,817 --> 00:17:46,417
He played that sound that only the children could hear,

336
00:17:46,417 --> 00:17:49,017
and let them know what order to tilt the pedestals.

337
00:17:49,017 --> 00:17:51,517
If nobody mentions anything regardless of the sound being heard,

338
00:17:51,517 --> 00:17:54,217
everything would seem normal.

339
00:17:54,217 --> 00:17:56,017
That's why you removed

340
00:17:56,017 --> 00:17:58,617
all the young staff from the TV crew, right?

341
00:17:58,617 --> 00:18:01,117
To avoid having anyone else hear that sound.

342
00:18:01,117 --> 00:18:06,617
You told us nothing about that mosquito sound, though.

343
00:18:06,617 --> 00:18:07,717
Sorry.

344
00:18:07,717 --> 00:18:10,917
Then, where are the horns of the giraffe?

345
00:18:10,917 --> 00:18:13,317
Oh, that's...

346
00:18:15,617 --> 00:18:18,317
Inside the hood of my parka!

347
00:18:18,317 --> 00:18:20,017
He pretended to take me,

348
00:18:20,017 --> 00:18:22,717
who was knocked out by the stun gun to the hospital

349
00:18:22,717 --> 00:18:26,317
and was planning to make it out of here, treasure and all!

350
00:18:26,317 --> 00:18:28,017
Although, I realized right away when I got up

351
00:18:28,017 --> 00:18:31,217
because of the weight of the treasure I felt.

352
00:18:31,217 --> 00:18:34,417
By the way, he used the florescent paint

353
00:18:34,417 --> 00:18:36,917
when the advisor handed over the keys

354
00:18:36,917 --> 00:18:40,617
to show us the statue of the giraffe.

355
00:18:40,617 --> 00:18:44,117
Back then, if he put florescent paint on the keys,

356
00:18:44,117 --> 00:18:45,617
then the keyholes where the keys are inserted

357
00:18:45,617 --> 00:18:47,717
will also have paint on them!

358
00:18:47,717 --> 00:18:50,417
Then, where's the real Inspector?

359
00:18:50,417 --> 00:18:54,417
Probably knocked out by a stun gun and around here some place.

360
00:18:56,717 --> 00:18:58,117
Open the door!

361
00:18:58,117 --> 00:19:01,817
The one that's inside is Kid disguised as me!

362
00:19:01,817 --> 00:19:03,617
-Why not let him in? -Open the door!

363
00:19:03,617 --> 00:19:09,217
But, if he came to get his accomplices out of here...

364
00:19:09,217 --> 00:19:13,317
If he wanted to, he would've done that long ago!

365
00:19:13,317 --> 00:19:15,717
-True! -Open the door!

366
00:19:15,717 --> 00:19:17,317
The one that's inside is Kid disguised as me!

367
00:19:17,317 --> 00:19:19,817
Okay, open the door!

368
00:19:28,117 --> 00:19:30,117
How about it, Kid?

369
00:19:30,117 --> 00:19:33,817
I've stamped all the adults except you.

370
00:19:33,817 --> 00:19:37,417
Now you can't disguise yourself as someone else!

371
00:19:37,417 --> 00:19:43,017
Because the one with no stamp on his face is you!

372
00:19:44,317 --> 00:19:47,517
So, this is it, for you.

373
00:19:47,517 --> 00:19:51,517
I wonder about that.

374
00:19:58,517 --> 00:20:00,917
-Genta? -Turn on the lights!

375
00:20:05,717 --> 00:20:07,017
Look for him!

376
00:20:07,017 --> 00:20:09,617
The one that doesn't have a stamp on his face!

377
00:20:09,617 --> 00:20:11,617
That's Kid!

378
00:20:11,617 --> 00:20:13,517
But, Inspector.

379
00:20:13,517 --> 00:20:16,417
Everybody's face is stamped.

380
00:20:16,417 --> 00:20:19,017
Kid is nowhere in sight!

381
00:20:19,017 --> 00:20:22,217
Impossible!

382
00:20:22,217 --> 00:20:25,117
Where the heck did he disappear to?

383
00:20:25,117 --> 00:20:27,717
He can't possibly disguise himself as a child.

384
00:20:27,717 --> 00:20:30,217
Hey!

385
00:20:30,217 --> 00:20:32,317
Help me!

386
00:20:32,317 --> 00:20:34,017
Genta!

387
00:20:34,017 --> 00:20:35,917
What happened? What's with that hole?

388
00:20:35,917 --> 00:20:37,817
I don't know!

389
00:20:37,817 --> 00:20:40,417
Somebody grabbed me in the dark

390
00:20:40,417 --> 00:20:43,417
and I was shoved into this hole!

391
00:20:43,417 --> 00:20:44,817
Come to think of it,

392
00:20:44,817 --> 00:20:47,617
Kid disguised as Inspector Nakamori

393
00:20:47,617 --> 00:20:49,917
was touching the floor.

394
00:20:49,917 --> 00:20:53,217
He probably set up a simple bomb at that time

395
00:20:53,217 --> 00:20:54,917
and opened a hole in the floor,

396
00:20:54,917 --> 00:20:58,017
used Genta as the lid and escaped under the floor.

397
00:20:58,017 --> 00:21:01,317
Okay! Kid is under the floor!

398
00:21:01,317 --> 00:21:02,717
Open it.

399
00:21:02,717 --> 00:21:04,717
Okay, I got it.

400
00:21:06,917 --> 00:21:09,617
Genta, you stay right there and don't move, okay?

401
00:21:09,617 --> 00:21:10,917
If somebody grabs your legs,

402
00:21:10,917 --> 00:21:13,417
shout really loud and let us know, okay?

403
00:21:13,417 --> 00:21:14,417
Okay.

404
00:21:14,417 --> 00:21:15,917
Hey! Did you find him?

405
00:21:15,917 --> 00:21:17,717
No, not yet.

406
00:21:17,717 --> 00:21:19,517
Hold it.

407
00:21:20,817 --> 00:21:23,517
Genta's 10 yen sized baldness, if I remember correctly...

408
00:21:30,317 --> 00:21:32,117
Thief Kid!

409
00:21:34,117 --> 00:21:36,317
I'll give this back to you.

410
00:21:36,317 --> 00:21:38,817
It wasn't what I after to begin with!

411
00:21:38,817 --> 00:21:40,817
When on earth did you...

412
00:21:40,817 --> 00:21:43,017
What about Genta?

413
00:21:43,017 --> 00:21:45,117
He's asleep under the floor.

414
00:21:45,117 --> 00:21:47,217
Fast asleep.

415
00:21:47,217 --> 00:21:48,717
I see.

416
00:21:48,717 --> 00:21:50,917
So he just wanted to prove

417
00:21:50,917 --> 00:21:53,217
that he could even disguise himself as a child.

418
00:21:53,217 --> 00:21:54,717
Right!

419
00:21:54,717 --> 00:21:56,617
I wanted to prove...

420
00:21:58,917 --> 00:22:02,517
that nothing is impossible for Thief Kid!

421
00:22:02,517 --> 00:22:05,417
-See you! -Hold it.

422
00:22:05,417 --> 00:22:07,817
You've forgotten something.

423
00:22:11,717 --> 00:22:13,217
That riot officer is Kid!

424
00:22:13,217 --> 00:22:14,717
-Nab him! -What?

425
00:22:14,717 --> 00:22:17,417
Kid?

426
00:22:17,417 --> 00:22:20,217
If I make it into the woods in this disguise,

427
00:22:20,217 --> 00:22:23,517
they wouldn't be able to tell me apart from the others.

428
00:23:46,417 --> 00:23:47,417
"1 hour later" -Thief Kid detected!

429
00:23:47,417 --> 00:23:49,917
6 kilometers west of the mountain temple.

430
00:23:53,117 --> 00:23:55,917
It's Kid! There he is!

431
00:23:55,917 --> 00:23:58,917
Why? How can they tell?

432
00:23:58,917 --> 00:24:00,717
"I have obtained the Giraffe horns. -Thief Kid"

433
00:24:00,717 --> 00:24:04,717
You're paying me back for passing me out, Kid!

434
00:24:06,417 --> 00:24:08,317
"Next Episode"

435
00:24:08,317 --> 00:24:09,717
I'm going to make French fries

436
00:24:09,717 --> 00:24:10,917
from the potatoes I dig up from the field

437
00:24:10,917 --> 00:24:13,317
and have them as snacks with my beer!

438
00:24:15,817 --> 00:24:17,717
Inspector, this dead body!

439
00:24:17,717 --> 00:24:21,317
Doesn't it look like it's pointing at his face with his index finger?

440
00:24:21,317 --> 00:24:26,117
Maybe he tried to let people know who killed him using his own face!

441
00:24:26,117 --> 00:24:30,117
Why does he also have a wound on his forehead?

442
00:24:31,017 --> 00:24:36,183
Next Conan, "Trap of the Roof Farm"

443
00:24:51,645 --> 00:24:53,745
Next Conan's Hint:

444
00:24:53,745 --> 00:24:56,045
"Scarecrow"

445
00:24:56,045 --> 00:24:57,845
Next time he may become you.

446
00:24:57,845 --> 00:24:59,045
Idiot, I'll never let him to that.

447
00:24:59,045 --> 00:25:00,745
Really?

